1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with processor allocation for grid architectures, which falls under the domain of distributed and parallel computing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents algorithms for minimizing the average number of communication hops, which involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves optimization of communication between processors, which can be viewed as a numerical optimization problem. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with communication between processors, which can be viewed as a network of nodes exchanging information. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper mentions the complexity of the processor allocation problem, which can be viewed as a computational complexity problem.
